{"name":"Combat","type":"ability","img":"icons/skills/melee/swords-parry-block-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 42\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Berserkers wear leather or furs and may carry shields. They can wield any weapon but prefer those suited to their animal totem; berserkers eschew missile weapons, but may hurl axes, daggers, or spears.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"berserker-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_00v93s2o1qg","path":"Berserker","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.GqQd4Cp1UrsQQneu"}},"_id":"3xiz8uQq5THTqYhI"}
{"name":"Encounter Bonus","type":"ability","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-peace-alliance.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 32\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Archons gain a +1 to reactions with beasts, elementals, and fey</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"archon-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_x9x1fncm659","path":"Archon, Elf","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"4RKmyqpy4jMYNoWR"}
{"name":"After Reaching 11th Level","type":"ability","img":"icons/environment/settlement/wizard-castle.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 55\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>At 11th level, a necromancer may build a stronghold attracting 1d4 1st level necromancers to serve as apprentices, where the necromancer (most likely) researches various paths to immortality.</p>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Their strongholds&mdash;usually remote towers or dungeons&mdash;are garrisoned by various skeletons, zombies, and golems created by the necromancer, all with standing orders to kill trespassers or capture them for experimentation in their unnatural studies.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"necromancer-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tgb4y2pvwv","path":"Necromancer","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.i6Cnmxuzew3gd3z7"}},"_id":"4T8dqxzGtRvCFno4"}
{"name":"Berserk","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/mouth-teeth-human.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 42\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>When wounded by a foe, berserkers erupt in a bloodthirsty fury (make a Control Berserk roll to resist). When compelled by this violent rage, berserkers charge headlong at their attacker, gaining +2 bonus to initiative, &ldquo;to-hit,&rdquo; and damage rolls. While berserk, ber- serkers enjoy 2 points of damage reduction and a +2 bonus to saves against a specific attack type (or a +1 bonus in an entire saving throw category). These attack types vary by beast cult, as defined by the referee (see below).</p>\n<p>In their berserk state, berserkers are heedless of risk, attacking the closest target in melee range (including allies; roll randomly if multiple tar- gets present themselves). Their abandon imposes a &ndash;4 AC penalty.</p>\n<p>When there are no more targets in melee range, or if a berserker strikes an ally, they may make a Control Berserk roll to return to normal. Each such attempt takes a full round of focused restraint (suffering a wound negates the attempt); once their fury has abated, a berserker must rest for 1 turn or suffer the penalty for not resting.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"berserker-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_00v93s2o1qg","path":"Berserker","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"4eXK0y3YqcgM5OEJ"}
{"name":"Divine Magic","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-blue%20.webp","data":{"description":"<p>See @Compendium[old-school-essentials.ose journals.rDANNhKgVb1HJk0V]{Magic}for full details on divine magic.</p>\n<p><strong>Holy symbol</strong>: Like clerics, elders must possess a holy symbol to cast divine spells.</p>\n<p><strong>Deity disfavour</strong>: Elders are bound by the same behavioural standards as clerics; if their alignment strays from that of their deity, they suffer Deity Disfavour.</p>\n<p><strong>Magical research</strong>:&nbsp;Elders may research new divine spells at any level; upon reaching 9th level, elders may create magic items and research other magical effects.</p>\n<p><strong>Spell casting</strong>:&nbsp;Elders may pray for divine spells, following the same rules for divine spell use as clerics.</p>\n<p><strong>Using magic items</strong>: Elders may use magic items reserved for clerics, including divine spell scrolls.</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"elder-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zyg4myb00sl","path":"Elder, Dwarf","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.Rzc3WPU7y9KAd1Ua"}},"_id":"5BU9J8QmywhEGE8e"}
{"name":"Wilderness Survival","type":"ability","img":"icons/weapons/bows/shortbow-recurve-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 38\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>In their home terrain, barbarians can track, hunt, forage, secure shelter, fashion tools, and set traps and snares. Failed attempts may be re-rolled, though each subsequent roll represents 1d4 hours of effort.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"barbarian-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_n70x22zlby","path":"Barbarian","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.mUvjxVs7SZNhegYZ"}},"_id":"5xUw2VP4YxL5t8qs"}
{"name":"Poison","type":"ability","img":"icons/consumables/potions/potion-bottle-skull-label-poison-teal.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 62\">\n<p>Assassins may concoct toxic compounds, either to coat weapons or for ingestion; the chance of success is based on level. A target may avoid the poison&rsquo;s effect with a successful saving throw. It takes 1 round to apply poison to a weapon, which remains potent for 1d6 rounds or until a target is hit; targets suffer weapon damage even if their poison save succeeds. Ingested poisons are applied to food or drink; damage is twice normal and manifest 1d6 turns after consumption.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div title=\"Page 63\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>&ldquo;Normal&rdquo; poison deals damage based on the assassin&rsquo;s level and <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">costs 500gp per dose. Optionally,</span></p>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>other poisons may be produced:</p>\n<p>&bull; <strong>Blindness</strong>: Target loses vision for 1d6 turns; 100gp/dose</p>\n<p>&bull; <strong>Death, instant</strong>: Target dies at end of round; 1,000gp/target&rsquo;s lev- el/dose</p>\n<p>&bull; <strong>Death, slow</strong>: Target suffers 1 damage die each turn up to the assassin&rsquo;s level; 1,000gp/dose</p>\n<p>&bull; <strong>Paralytic</strong>: Target paralysed for 1d6 turns; 250gp/dose</p>\n<p>&bull;<strong> Sleep</strong>: Target falls unconscious for 2d6 turns; 250gp/dose</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"assassin-bxo","roll":"1d6","rollType":"below","rollTarget":1,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_re5zb6cjd28","path":"Assassin","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.7CuWqxXlSLCrrquS"}},"_id":"7ulgWOduOl87mWzK"}
