{"name":"Divine Power","type":"ability","img":"icons/equipment/neck/amulet-carved-stone-hammer.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 26\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Each elder clan receives a special ability related to their deity&rsquo;s sphere of influence (q.v., &ldquo;Divine Powers by Deity,&rdquo; below). The referee is encouraged to modify these powers to suit the setting&rsquo;s dwarven immortals, with a total value of 400 XP to conform with the base XP and level progression table on the facing page.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div title=\"Page 27\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Divine Powers by Deity </strong></p>\n<p>Each deity provides its elders with different divine powers; these are setting specific, but the following archetypes may inspire the referee:</p>\n<p>&bull; Dwarf Pantheon (general): +1 reactions with dwarfs, 2 bonus spell levels per day</p>\n<p>&bull; Greed: 2/6 chance to hide un- derground, Backstab or 4 Thief Skills as thief of equal level</p>\n<p>&bull; Luck: +2 save vs. category of player&rsquo;s choice</p>\n<p>&bull; Protection: +2 AC vs. goblin-folk, 2 bonus spell levels per day</p>\n<p>&bull; War: +1 initiative vs. goblin-folk, +1 to allies&rsquo; morale</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"elder-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zyg4myb00sl","path":"Elder, Dwarf","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.g3rFjdLhEBbqGCeu"}},"_id":"BKBILEeikWkdnB8V"}
