{"name":"Restrictions","type":"ability","img":"icons/skills/social/trading-justice-scale-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 40\">\n<div title=\"Page 48\">\n<div title=\"Page 56\">\n<p><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Alignment</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">: Scouts have a respect for life that restricts them to Lawful or Neutral alignment.</span></p>\n<div title=\"Page 64\">\n<div title=\"Page 66\">\n<p><strong>Wild</strong>: Scouts dislike the noise and bustle of urban environments, which is fine since people usually view them with suspicion as wild-folk. In any settlement larger than a village, scouts suffer a &ndash;2 penalty to all reaction rolls.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"scout-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yykl5k5ajoq","path":"Scout","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.GqQd4Cp1UrsQQneu"}},"_id":"DXQxcHSt9mGwetDe"}
{"name":"After Reaching 9th Level","type":"ability","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-open-red.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 63\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>When an assassin achieves 9th level, they may establish an Assassins&rsquo; Guild, attracting 1d4 1st level assas- sins and 2d6 1st level fighters (or thugs, pg. 59). These apprentices serve to the best of their ability, but those apprehended or killed are not replaced. Each level after 9th attracts an additional 0-3 (1d4&ndash;1) 1st level assassins and 1d6 fighters.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"assassin-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_re5zb6cjd28","path":"Assassin","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.nMS4lDk0nVmdXqo7"}},"_id":"DrRn7sm8zvFpQD41"}
{"name":"Wilderness Survival","type":"ability","img":"icons/weapons/bows/shortbow-recurve-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 38\">\n<div title=\"Page 48\">\n<div title=\"Page 66\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Scouts can track, hunt, forage, secure shelter, fashion tools, and set traps and snares with a successful Wilderness Survival roll. Failed attempts may be re-rolled, though each subsequent roll represents 1d6 hours of effort.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"scout-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yykl5k5ajoq","path":"Scout","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.mUvjxVs7SZNhegYZ"}},"_id":"EDEwGa3WogsH8g5J"}
{"name":"Animal Companion","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/nature/wolf-paw-glow-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 40\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 40\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">Beast-talkers have animal companions instead of NPC retainers (number and morale based on the beast-talker&rsquo;s CHA). During any encounter with normal or </span><span style=\"font-family: TwCenMT; font-size: 10pt;\">giant animals, a reaction roll of 12+ indicates the animal will become the beast-talker&rsquo;s companion if invited.</span></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">Animal companions communicate empathically with the beast-talker. Within 30&rsquo; per level, a companion also imparts a special ability for 1 turn or encounter (q.v., Appendix G); only one ability may be used at a time, each once per day. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">Each companion gains an improvement when the beast-talker gains a level: </span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"beast-talker-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4jlmlo6pda2","path":"Beast-talker","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.GqQd4Cp1UrsQQneu"}},"_id":"GXLemZaZXbmgXawa"}
