{"name":"Arcane Magic","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-blue%20.webp","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Arcane Magic</strong></p>\n<p>See @Compendium[old-school-essentials.ose journals.rDANNhKgVb1HJk0V]{Magic} for full details on <em>arcane magic</em>.</p>\n<p><strong>Magical research</strong>:Archons of any level may research new spells. They cannot create magic items or research other magical effects.</p>\n<p><strong>Spell casting</strong>: Archons must bear a talisman (ring, brooch, pin, etc.) that signifies to primal powers their right to engage in arcane pacts. An ar- chon&rsquo;s talisman is unique; spells cannot be loosed without it. Replacing a lost talisman involves a major quest. <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Archons gain arcane spells up to 5th level through pacts made with primal beings. To cast a spell, archons must make a Spell Casting roll to invoke the pact (see Arcane Pacts). Elementals conjured by an archon have maximum hit points, and if their concentration is broken, an archon may make a reaction roll to regain control.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Using magic items</strong>: As spell casters, archons can use arcane scrolls and magic items reserved for elves.</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"archon-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_x9x1fncm659","path":"Archon, Elf","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.DYhicOmmfblJdemw"}},"_id":"GmqbYyr7wpzHKsFY"}
