{"name":"Control Golems","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/magical/spirit-fear-energy-pink.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 54\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Necromancers may make a reaction roll when encountering golems not of their own making; on a reaction result of 12 or more, the necromancer may control the golem as if it were their own crea- tion for up to 1 turn per level.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"necromancer-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tgb4y2pvwv","path":"Necromancer","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QQs03Fvsp0mLVRdG"}
{"name":"After Reaching 9th Level","type":"ability","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-open-red.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 65\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>At 9th level, a bard may establish a college wherein they teach history, composition, recitation, and instrumentation. The college attracts 2d6 nobles and 1d4 1st level bards each semester, which is typically 4-6 continuous months during which the bard cannot participate in adventures. Apprentices may accompany the bard on excursions but count against the bard&rsquo;s retainer limit. Assume that tuition from nobles covers the cost of the college&rsquo;s upkeep.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"bard-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ampjsspqo9d","path":"Bard","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.Tbxii0fa5C1V6Ore"}},"_id":"RC2BTz6KzZFilRGO"}
