{"name":"Superstitious","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/perception/orb-eye-scrying.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 38\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Barbarians consider arcane magic taboo and suffer a &ndash;2 penalty to saving throws against any arcane effect. They will not knowingly use any item, weapon, or armour enchanted with arcane magic.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"barbarian-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_n70x22zlby","path":"Barbarian","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.UajAB2ZFOcz5ui7W"}},"_id":"Z3lLxMSPdPBYTcGY"}
{"name":"Assassinate","type":"ability","img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-skull-white.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 62\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>The assassin&rsquo;s trademark skill, assassinate can instantly kill a target with a devastating strike. When attacking an unaware human-sized or smaller opponent, an assassin receives a +4 bonus &ldquo;to-hit.&rdquo; If the attack succeeds, damage is multiplied by the target&rsquo;s (descend- ing) AC plus the assassin&rsquo;s level (min- imum factor of x1). Targets larger</p>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>than human-sized may be assassinated only if their level/hit die is equal or less than the assassin&rsquo;s and they have a vulnerable spot on their body (i.e., brain, throat, heart, life crystal, etc.). Undead beings and constructs (e.g., golems) cannot be assassinated.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"assassin-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_re5zb6cjd28","path":"Assassin","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.gD5xRVEheiQdPbcv"}},"_id":"ZsDy5hRBwkS2pTtb"}
{"name":"Divine Magic","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-blue%20.webp","data":{"description":"<p>See @Compendium[old-school-essentials.ose journals.rDANNhKgVb1HJk0V]{Magic}for full details on divine magic.</p>\n<p><strong>Holy symbol</strong>:&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">A shaman carries a fetish for each of their spirit guides (a tooth, claw, pelt, etc.); this object is required to cast spells, speak with animals, and shapechange.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Deity disfavour</strong>:&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Shamans may be Neutral or Chaotic. Neutral shamans embrace the harmonious aspects of their spirit animal; Chaotic shamans emulate their guides&rsquo; survival instincts and displays of power.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Any alignment shift or a drastic deviation from their animal spirit&rsquo;s guidance causes the guide to forsake the shaman until proper atonement is made.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Magical research</strong>:&nbsp;The shaman may appeal to their spirit guides to aid in magical research as a cleric of equal level.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Spell casting</strong>:&nbsp;A shaman casts spells as a cleric of equal level but selects from a &ldquo;druidic&rdquo; or nature-oriented</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div title=\"Page 21\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>spell list. Shamans cast spells as rituals, which require a material sacri- fice valuable to their animal guide equal to 10gp per spell level (food, milk, nesting material, etc.). Casting a spell requires 1 round per spell level of uninterrupted meditation.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Using magic items</strong>: Shamans may use magic items reserved for clerics, including divine spell scrolls.</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"shaman-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zlg7vwx3m5","path":"Shaman","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.Rzc3WPU7y9KAd1Ua"}},"_id":"a42teoirHrnGhvZA"}
