{"name":"After Reaching 9th Level","type":"ability","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-open-red.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 67\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>When a scout reaches 9th level, they may build a fortified outpost within familiar territory. The outpost&rsquo;s cost is halved due to local support, and when completed attracts 3d6 1st level fighters and 1d4+1 1st level apprentice scout. At each experience level gained after 9th, the scout attracts an additional 1d6 fighters and 0-3 (1d4&ndash;1) 1st level scouts.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"scout-bxo","roll":"2d6","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yykl5k5ajoq","path":"Scout","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.Tbxii0fa5C1V6Ore"}},"_id":"cEKG2kqFG30ogyeS"}
