{"name":"Call of the Wild","type":"ability","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/wolf-howl-moon-gray.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 40\">\n<div title=\"Page 40\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div title=\"Page 40\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Beast-talkers may summon animals for aid. Animals arrive in 1d6 rounds and help to the best of their ability (type and num- ber as a random animal encounter for the current terrain). In their home range, rolls are made at +1; rolls to summon a specific animal type are made at &ndash;1. If summoned animals suffer injury, all further rolls are penalised by &ndash;2 until redress is given.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"beast-talker-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4jlmlo6pda2","path":"Beast-talker","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.GqQd4Cp1UrsQQneu"}},"_id":"eiVqxElnZRogYb6P"}
