{"name":"After Reaching 9th Level","type":"ability","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-open-red.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 19\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>At 9th level, a crusader may establish a stronghold as a chapter of their fighting order. The fortification at- tracts 20-120 (2d6x10) 1st level fighters, 2d6 crusaders, and 2-5 (1d4+1) clerics of the order&rsquo;s parent church (levels 1d4 each). The strong- hold must provide succour to church officials and allies, as well as aid in the defence against the infidel. At each experience level after 9th, the crusader attracts 10-60 fighters, 1d6 crusaders, and 1d2 clerics.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div title=\"Page 19\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Fighting Order Missions </strong></p>\n<p>&bull; Reclaim holy land<br />&bull; Purge the realm of infidels<br />&bull; Ensure the safety of pilgrims,</p>\n<p>missionaries, or evangelists<br />&bull; Find, recover, or destroy an arte-</p>\n<p>fact<br />&bull; Protect a holy site or prophet<br />&bull; Prepare for divine visitation<br />&bull; Clear the way for prophecy<br />&bull; Bring infidels to justice<br />&bull; Locate a mortal incarnation of</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>the divine</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"crusader-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sgyztgev1h8","path":"Crusader","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.BlDloVzjEkYGiFfS"}},"_id":"lTH1JPWSuX6xKW8m"}
{"name":"After Reaching 10th Level","type":"ability","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-open-red.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 33\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>At 10th level, an archon may build a stronghold dedicated to the service of primal beings. The stronghold must be built in a natural setting and gains the favour of all beasts, elementals, and fey in the local hex. Once established, and at each level thereafter, the stronghold attracts the service of 2d6 1st level elves, plus one archon for every six elves.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"archon-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_x9x1fncm659","path":"Archon, Elf","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.rZtKDDpny2XtW3Aq"}},"_id":"ldtuVwcaPP6i6v70"}
{"name":"Disguise","type":"ability","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/mask-wood-tan.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 62\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Assassins may alter their appearance to look like someone else. Rolls are made whenever the disguise must be convincing, with a cumulative penalty of &ndash;1 if the disguise is beyond the assassin&rsquo;s race, build, or sex, or if the disguise mimics a specific individual.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"assassin-bxo","roll":"1d6","rollType":"below","rollTarget":1,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_re5zb6cjd28","path":"Assassin","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.oR7eAPFWdzPNGARb"}},"_id":"lwAuJRpw3w3osJU1"}
{"name":"Detect Construction Tricks","type":"ability","img":"icons/commodities/stone/paver-brick-brown.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">As expert miners, dwarves have a 2-in-6 chance of being able to detect new construction, sliding walls, or sloping passages when searching.</span></p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"elder-bxo","roll":"1d6","rollType":"below","rollTarget":2,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zyg4myb00sl","path":"Elder, Dwarf","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.DyoBG8eL9277LgbH"}},"_id":"mUAr199xzyWrdKbq"}
{"name":"Hear noise (HN)","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/symbols/question-stone-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<p>In a quiet environment (e.g. not in combat), a thief may attempt to listen at a door or to hear the sounds of something (e.g. a wandering monster) approaching.</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"barbarian-bxo","roll":"1d6","rollType":"below","rollTarget":2,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_n70x22zlby","path":"Barbarian","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.1C8cxmp5t55hUARu"}},"_id":"mseCUfGs6B0ZBf9M"}
{"name":"After Reaching 9th Level","type":"ability","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-open-red.webp","data":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 39\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">When a barbarian achieves 9</span><span style=\"font-size: 6.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT'; vertical-align: 3.000000pt;\">th </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">level, they may summon a horde of 1</span><span style=\"font-size: 6.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT'; vertical-align: 3.000000pt;\">st </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">level barbarians, equal in size to their current XP divided by 1,000 (e.g., a 10</span><span style=\"font-size: 6.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT'; vertical-align: 3.000000pt;\">th </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">level barbarian&rsquo;s horde numbers at least 390 warriors). The horde also includes aides equal to the barbarian&rsquo;s maximum number of retainers (though they don&rsquo;t count against the retainer limit). Aides are determined by the referee: </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'SymbolMT';\">&bull; </span><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">Sub-chief: Barbarian &ldquo;lieutenants,&rdquo; half the character&rsquo;s level;</span></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">each sub-chief adds +1 to the </span><span style=\"font-family: TwCenMT; font-size: 10pt;\">horde&rsquo;s morale.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;\">\n<li style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'SymbolMT';\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">Druid or Shaman: Divine practi</span><span style=\"font-family: TwCenMT; font-size: 10pt;\">tioners of the barbarian&rsquo;s spiritu- al faith, equal to the barbarian&rsquo;s level.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'SymbolMT';\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">Specialist: Any NPC with a pro- fessional skill useful to the horde. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">Hordes are raised to achieve a spe- cific goal (e.g., defeat the invaders, sack a city, kill the dragon), and disband after one week per level of the barbarian or when the task is complete (whichever comes first). </span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"barbarian-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_n70x22zlby","path":"Barbarian","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.bX8ZYinwnzbKi52Y"}},"_id":"n0gPJeKlywo8BNJk"}
