{"name":"Hiding","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-beast-eyes-green.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 48\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Wardens have a 9/10 chance to hide in the wilderness; unlike other halflings, they do not have the ability to hide in dungeons.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"warden-bxo","roll":"1d10","rollType":"below","rollTarget":9,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sowvayswi5","path":"Warden, Halfling","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.GrMAzajhQLNeTOZz"}},"_id":"nrflE4IxGgN2gb9m"}
{"name":"Move silently (MS)","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/nature/stealth-hide-beast-eyes-green.webp","data":{"description":"<p>&nbsp;A warden may attempt to sneak past enemies unnoticed.</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"warden-bxo","roll":"1d100","rollType":"below","rollTarget":20,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sowvayswi5","path":"Warden, Halfling","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.e2QXLtpEAvVC644l"}},"_id":"LMEhXHfFD8NgEX7l"}
{"name":"Restrictions","type":"ability","img":"icons/skills/social/trading-justice-scale-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 40\">\n<div title=\"Page 48\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Alignment</strong>: A warden&rsquo;s alignment cannot be opposite that of the sheriff they have sworn to serve.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div title=\"Page 48\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Badge of Office</strong>: All wardens are given a badge of office by the local sheriff to signify their authority (e.g., a brooch, pin, feathered cap, shield device, etc.). The warden must display this badge to gain their reac- tion roll bonus (see below).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div title=\"Page 48\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Pledge</strong>: Wardens are pledged to serve the local sheriff; failure to do so strips the warden of their special abilities (rendering them a &ldquo;normal&rdquo; halfling) until some effort is undertaken to regain the community&rsquo;s confidence.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"warden-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sowvayswi5","path":"Warden, Halfling","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.GqQd4Cp1UrsQQneu"}},"_id":"D8ZKglxUqJ1sdH2b"}
{"name":"Special Foes by Terrain","type":"ability","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/terrain-forest-gray.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 49\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>A warden&rsquo;s choice of special foe varies by their community&rsquo;s terrain type; non-exhaustive options include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hills</strong>: Animals, bandits, giants, goblins, kobolds, Neanderthals, orcs, trolls</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Forest</strong>: Animals, bandits, bug- bears, gnolls, (hob)goblins, ogres, orcs, trolls</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Plains</strong>: Animals, bandits, bug- bears, gnolls, (hob)goblins, no- mads, ogres, orcs, trolls</li>\n<li><strong>Coastal/Lake/River</strong>: Animals, buccaneers, bugbears, gnolls, lizard men, ogres, orcs, trolls</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"warden-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sowvayswi5","path":"Warden, Halfling","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"y8gBVVhE2KW7YmYj"}
{"name":"Wilderness Survival","type":"ability","img":"icons/weapons/bows/shortbow-recurve-yellow.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 38\">\n<div title=\"Page 48\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Outdoors, wardens can track, hunt, forage, secure shelter, fashion tools, and set traps and snares. Failed attempts may be re-rolled, though each subsequent roll represents 1d6 hours of effort.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"warden-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sowvayswi5","path":"Warden, Halfling","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.mUvjxVs7SZNhegYZ"}},"_id":"h1VO27tHMdubHGoy"}
