{"_id":"PQbLkH7c6uf0Eamh","name":"Arcane Pacts","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/symbols/rune-sigil-horned-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 33\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Arcane pacts are ancient agreements with primal beings, who grant magic spells in exchange for mortal vitality in the form of hit points.</p>\n<p>Each day, an archon may wield 1 spell level per experience level (e.g., <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">a 4</span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">th </span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">level archon could cast four 1</span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">st </span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">level spells, two 2</span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">nd </span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">level spells, or any combination not exceeding four total spell levels).</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div title=\"Page 33\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>To release a spell, an archon appeals to a primal being for aid with a Spell Casting roll. If the roll succeeds, the spell is &ldquo;cast&rdquo;; if the roll fails, the appeal is ignored, and the spell effect does not manifest. Either way, they attempt counts against the archon&rsquo;s daily spell limit.</p>\n<p>Archons gain a +1 bonus to their Spell Casting rolls by sacrificing hit points equal to the level of the spell to be cast (e.g., for a 2nd level spell, a 2hp sacrifice grants a +1 bonus, 4hp grants +2, etc.). Hit points sacrificed in this way heal normally.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"archon-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_x9x1fncm659","path":"Archon, Elf","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.DYhicOmmfblJdemw"}}}
{"_id":"GXLemZaZXbmgXawa","name":"Animal Companion","type":"ability","img":"icons/magic/nature/wolf-paw-glow-orange.webp","data":{"description":"<div title=\"Page 40\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 40\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">Beast-talkers have animal companions instead of NPC retainers (number and morale based on the beast-talker&rsquo;s CHA). During any encounter with normal or </span><span style=\"font-family: TwCenMT; font-size: 10pt;\">giant animals, a reaction roll of 12+ indicates the animal will become the beast-talker&rsquo;s companion if invited.</span></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">Animal companions communicate empathically with the beast-talker. Within 30&rsquo; per level, a companion also imparts a special ability for 1 turn or encounter (q.v., Appendix G); only one ability may be used at a time, each once per day. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\">Each companion gains an improvement when the beast-talker gains a level: </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.000000pt; font-family: 'TwCenMT';\"><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/AnimalCompanionImprovements.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"202\" height=\"238\" /></span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"white","requirements":"beast-talker-bxo","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4jlmlo6pda2","path":"Beast-talker","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.old-school-essentials.ose abilities.GqQd4Cp1UrsQQneu"}}}
